-- pg_turbovec v1.25.0 -- Gap-B fix: turbovec.hi_dim_rerank, a
-- dimension-aware exact-L2 rerank-window widening for high-dim recall.
--
-- This file is a *reference mirror*. The authoritative install
-- script is generated by `cargo pgrx schema`.
--
-- NO wire-format change (stays VERSION 6, byte-identical to v1.24.0).
-- Existing v4/v5/v6 indexes all decode unchanged. NO REINDEX.
--
-- New SQL surface (additive, minor bump): one new GUC,
-- `turbovec.hi_dim_rerank` (enum: off | auto | on; default auto).
-- No new operators, types, functions, or opclasses.
--
-- What it does (scan-side only): the offline Gap-B investigation
-- established that the
-- high-dimensional recall gap (e.g. GIST-1M/960d capping ~0.86) is
-- NOT retrieval-bound -- the true nearest neighbours DO land in the
-- probed cells (measured cell recall 0.98-0.996 at probes 64-128) --
-- but an IN-CELL quantized-RANKING loss: the lossy 4-bit score is
-- noisy enough at high dim that a true neighbour often sits at rank
-- ~200-800 within the probed cells, below a small search_k. The cure
-- is to fetch a WIDER candidate set so the always-on exact-L2 reorder
-- recheck (xs_recheckorderby) re-ranks enough survivors to recover
-- the true top-k. Measured: an SQ4 analog lifts R@10 0.666 -> 0.978
-- at 960-dim by reranking ~800 candidates instead of ~64.
--
-- It must NOT blanket-widen (low dim already plateaus by search_k~=25,
-- so widening there is pure latency tax), so `auto` applies a
-- DIM-SCALED candidate floor of clamp(dim, 256..=1024) ONLY for
-- indexes with dim >= 256, and only ever RAISES the count -- an
-- explicit search_k/oversample override past the floor always wins.
-- SIFT-128 is untouched; GIST-960 / OpenAI-1536 / the 512-768d
-- families get the wider window automatically. `on` applies the floor
-- regardless of dim; `off` is the pre-fix behaviour (honour
-- search_k/oversample exactly). The result set is identical to
-- setting search_k/oversample by hand to the same candidate count.
--
-- Migration: `ALTER EXTENSION pg_turbovec UPDATE TO '1.25.0';`.
-- No REINDEX, no wire change. The new default (auto) improves high-dim
-- recall out of the box at a small high-dim-only latency cost; set
-- `turbovec.hi_dim_rerank = off` to restore exact pre-1.25.0
-- scan-candidate behaviour.
